name: RESIST!
description: This is the old railroad bridge crossing the Colorado River near downtown Austin, Texas captured in 1963. This was during the height of the Civil Rights and Anti-war movement and demonstrations, and the RESIST! graffiti on the bridge for “all to see” was highly controversial at the time. This is the first NFT minting by a 75 year old technophile (called an “egghead” during the day) and the first of a series of never before seen historical photos from this era. This original photograph was taken on 35mm Ektachrome with a Praktica FX2 SLR.
